cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper involves the use of camera-equipped drones to explore and reconstruct 3D maps, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method involves learning a utility function using a 3D convolutional neural network, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the evaluation of the method involves large 3D models of urban scenes, which could also fall under the category of computer graphics (cs.GR).
